intro: Hymenatherum pentachaetum, commonly known as the five-bracted satinwood, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the legume family, Fabaceae, and is characterized by its small, fragrant white or pink flowers. The plant has compound leaves with an odd number of leaflets, typically five, and produces small, woody pods that contain seeds. It is often found in sandy or rocky soils in woodland habitats.
